text: Jan Olaf Roaldset (born 28 March 1946) is a Norwegian ski jumper. He was born in Molde and represented the club IL Hjelset-Fram. He competed at the 1968 Winter Olympics in Grenoble, where he placed 21st in the normal hill and 13th in the large hill. ==References== Category:1946 births Category:Living people Category:People from Molde Category:Norwegian male ski jumpers Category:Olympic ski jumpers of Norway Category:Ski jumpers at the 1968 Winter Olympics
